g.text: Requirements for issuance
plaintiff must come with "clean hands"
must not be delayed in action
must not negatively affect innocent purchaser
plaintiff paid meaningful consideration (under seal or nominal don't apply)
plaintiff must be a party against whom the remedy would be awarded if he was defendant
Types of Equitable Remedies
Specific performance: order requiring defendant to do an act (e.g. transact) provided defendant need not be supervised
Injunction: must include negative covenant (promise not to do something)
Interlocutory injunction: temporary injunction preventing immediate harm
Recission: setting aside, putting parties back from where they started
Quantum meruit
